<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/447910-i-am-a-little-confused-about-the-ending-i">I am a little confused about the ending. I think the book was well written, and the author is extremely intelligent, but at times I feel the book could been cut in half. Is the ending just telling you what led up to everything that happened and why it happened? I already knew all this. Am I missing something in the ending I should know about?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_447910'><a id="like_count_community_question_447910" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/447910?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">15 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F17262100-the-lowland">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/447910-i-am-a-little-confused-about-the-ending-i">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/447910-i-am-a-little-confused-about-the-ending-i">See all 11 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/1441529-tamie"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/1441529-tamie">Tamie</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    The way I read the ending was that as the book unfolded we heard everybody's story from their point of view. The only one we hadn't heard from was Uda<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    The way I read the ending was that as the book unfolded we heard everybody's story from their point of view. The only one we hadn't heard from was Udayan. I thought it was profound of the author to include his version of events regarding the night he died. It painted him as a more complicated person who actually understood that what he had done to the policeman and the way he manipulated his wife, was wrong. It made him seem more real to me. And it completed the story. It also painted a more complicated relationship between him and his wife, which made me appreciate her story more.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
